 More winners have emerged in the ongoing Globacom’s Joy Unlimited Extravaganza Promo as lucky subscribers went home with a brand-new car and home appliances including refrigerators, televisions and generating sets. A 37-year-old insurance executive, Adewale Kafayat Morenikeji was last week presented the key to a new Kia Rio car by Telecommunications solutions provider, Globacom, having emerged winner in the ongoing promo Sixty-six other winners were also presented home appliances including 23 television sets, 20 refrigerators and 23 power generating sets. Mrs Adewale’s car gift is the 13th brand new Kia Rio car won so far in the ongoing promo while thousands of home appliances had gone to lucky subscribers. “I am very excited as today I have become a Glo Ambassador and I will spread the news about the good deeds of Glo as well as convince every Nigerian I meet to join the Glo network,” she said. In his address at the 16th prize presentation to winners of the promo at GLOWORLD, Cele Bus Stop in Lagos; the Regional Manager, Sales at Glo, Abdulrasaq Ande commended subscribers for their support and loyalty over the years; saying, they remain the company’s pillar of strength. According to him, the testimonials from winners have been overwhelming, as Nigerians across the country have been positively impacted by the promo, which he said was primarily unveiled to commemorate the Glo’s 18th anniversary and to appreciate the over 54 million subscribers on the network for their loyalty over the years. He said, “We still have two brand new cars and hundreds of home appliances to give out before the end of the promo. You could still be among the next set of winners. “To qualify for the weekly draws in this promo, subscribers are required to recharge their Glo lines with a minimum of N500 while N2,000 recharge in a calendar month qualifies subscribers for the monthly draws for the grand prize of Kia Rio saloon car.”